title: What Next for Yes Bank? | CA Rachana Ranade | #shorts
description: Description:- In March 2020, a consortium of investors led by the State Bank of India infused Rs.10,000 Crore to bail out the bank. As a part of this, SBI bought shares worth Rs.6,050 Crores for a 48% stake. Further, as a part of the ‚ÄúYes Bank Limited Reconstruction Scheme, 2020‚Äù shareholders holding more than 100 shares were locked in for 3 years for up to 75% of their shareholding, with SBI being required to hold a minimum of 26% during the lock-in period. SBI initially held 48.21%, which was reduced to 30% in June 2020 and 26.14% in December 2022. Currently, SBI is holding 26.14% worth Rs.12,402 crores. The lock-in period for SBI ended on March 6, 2023, and it has not sold any shares since then. The lock-in period for other stakeholders is ending on March 13, 2023. This is an important development in the banking industry and the future of Yes Bank. We will have to wait and see how this impacts the bank and its shareholders.

title: STOP Working for MONEY | How to RETIRE in YOUR 30s | Finance With Sharan
description:
When we hear the term retiring, we think of someone who is in their 60s, in an old age home, and not able to enjoy the money that they have worked so hard to gather.  

Well you are wrong. Retiring doesn't have to be sad. In this video we talk about how you can retire early, how to invest your money so that you can retire early, and what to take care of after you have invested your money.

title: The Big Mac Index Hota Kya Hai? üçî
description:
Have you ever wondered what the cost of an item you consume in India üáÆüá≥ would be abroad?

 If you have traveled abroad, you would have noticed that the price of the same goods varies between countries. 

For example, a Big Mac üçî costs 5$ approx. in the US, which is equivalent to INR. 400. However, the cost of the same burger in India is just INR. 250. Do the math and you get 1$ coming to just INR 50 INR compared to the INR 80 exchange rate. 

This is because the Big mac is cheaper to produce in India. The cost of rent, salaries etc., are much more affordable in India than in the US üá∫üá∏, even though they produce the same burger. 

This is called the Big Mac Index, where the cost of big macs is used to determine the purchasing power parity (PPP).

The PPP compares the value of all goods and services produced between 2 countries and ensures them with one another. By comparing PPP, we can compare income from different countries concerning your spending power. For context, the PPP between the US and India is 1$ = INR 22. 

‚úÖ So the next time you are chowing down on a burger, remember this reel and that you‚Äôd have paid more for the same burger somewhere else.

title: How Hospitals Are SCAMMING YOU
description:
Don‚Äôt you get the feeling that there is little difference left between five star hotels üåü and the so-called state-of-the-art hospitals?

Both give five star service, and if you are not aware, these hospitals charge a bomb & too, sometimes even double the average cost. üí£ 

Yes, you guessed it right. 

The insurance companies don‚Äôt like it. * They put a clause called ‚ÄúUS‚Äù or ‚Äúusual, reasonable and customary‚Äù clause. ‚ùé 

Meaning, they will only cover the average cost for that kind of procedure in your geographical area.

A difference of 10-20% percentage is fine, but not beyond that. This is why so many claims get settled only partially. ( And it is difficult to fight for the exorbitant cost that the hospital charged you. üè•

title: Send Money Internationally Without Banks Or Foreign Exchange
description:
Humans have been using paper for money starting from the early 7th century. But of late, crypto-currencies have seen a rise. üîê

The government is not a huge fan of crypto due to the lack of regulation, so they made their very own crypto called e-RUPI, and here‚Äôs what it means for us. 

An e-RUPI is a digital token equivalent to our fiat currency i.e., the Indian Rupee. ‚Çπ‚Çπ‚Çπ

Since they are digital money, the cost and speed of transactions are vastly reduced, ensuring seamless service over long distances at a cheaper cost üí∏

An added advantage of digitizing money is that you can program it to ensure it is utilized only for a given purpose. The government can utilize this feature to ensure that the money goes to the scheme as planned and not elsewhere. However, there is a fear that the government can program the money to monitor the public and control our spending.

description:
** A differential equation of first order and first degree can be written as f( x, y, dy/dx) = 0.
* For any differential equations it is possible to find the general solution and particular solution.
* If in an equation it is possible to collect all the terms of x and dx on one side and all the terms of y and dy on the other side, then the variables are said to be separable. Thus the general form of such an equation is,
f(x)dx = g(y)dy (or) f(x)dx + g(y)dy = 0.

f(x)dx = g(y)dy (or) f(x)dx + g(y)dy = 0.

description:
** A differential equation of first order and first degree can be written as f( x, y, dy/dx) = 0.
* For any differential equations it is possible to find the general solution and particular solution.
* If in an equation it is possible to collect all the terms of x and dx on one side and all the terms of y and dy on the other side, then the variables are said to be separable. Thus the general form of such an equation is,
f(x)dx = g(y)dy (or) f(x)dx + g(y)dy = 0.

title: What is Clean Plant Program ? Geography & Environment Current Affairs by Sudarshan Gurjar | UPSC
description:
In this video, educator Sudarshan Gurjar discusses the Union Government's plan to launch an Atmanirbhar Clean Plant Program for the horticulture industry. 
The program, which is expected to be launched soon, aims to promote clean and sustainable practices in horticulture to reduce pollution and environmental damage.
He provides an overview of the horticulture industry in India and the challenges it faces in terms of pollution and sustainability. 
He then discusses the various initiatives under the Atmanirbhar Clean Plant Program that are aimed at promoting clean and sustainable practices in horticulture, such as the use of precision farming techniques and reducing the use of harmful pesticides and fertilizers.
Throughout the video, He offers insights into the potential impact of the program on the horticulture industry, including the benefits for farmers, consumers, and the environment. 
He also discusses the challenges that may arise in implementing the program, such as the need for greater government support and investment in new technologies.
Whether you're a farmer, industry professional, or simply interested in sustainable practices in horticulture, this video provides valuable insights into the upcoming Atmanirbhar Clean Plant Program and its potential impact on the industry. 
So tune in and join the conversation on promoting clean and sustainable horticulture practices in India!
